    <node id="Large Language Models">
      <data key="d0">Large Language Models</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Large Language Models are advanced AI systems that can process and generate human-like language. They are widely used across various sectors, necessitating robust evaluation datasets. These models are capable of long-context reasoning and have applications in various domains, including code generation, where they rely on detailed and well-formed task descriptions.

Large Language Models are a type of artificial intelligence model that can process and understand human language. They are increasingly deployed AI systems whose outputs can be highly sensitive to routine input variation. This sensitivity highlights the complexity of these systems, which can misbehave in various ways, including training-time backdoors, jailbreaks, and prompt injections.

Moreover, Large Language Models are agentic problem solvers that rely on external, reusable skills to handle tasks beyond their native parametric capabilities. This characteristic underscores their ability to adapt and learn from diverse sources, making them a valuable tool in various fields. However, their reliance on external skills also raises concerns about their potential for misuse and the need for robust evaluation and testing procedures.

In addition to their general capabilities, Large Language Models have been integrated into Multi-Agent Systems to enhance collaborative problem-solving capabilities. They have also been used as a context for evaluating the Perceived Cooperativity and Teaming Perception Scales. Furthermore, Large Language Models excel at general code generation but struggle with task-level coordination patterns and API-level parameter constraints.

Large Language Models can be augmented by Process Reward Models, and they have demonstrated strong reasoning capabilities in general knowledge question answering. However, they struggle with temporal information. Despite these limitations, Large Language Models are a type of artificial intelligence model that has become increasingly important in natural language processing.&lt;SEP&gt;Large Language Models are artificial intelligence models used as bidding agents in repeated 6G spectrum auctions with budget constraints.&lt;SEP&gt;Large Language Models are a type of AI model that reveal inherent and distinctive personas through dialogue.&lt;SEP&gt;Large Language Models are complex systems increasingly deployed in high-stakes and operational settings, requiring evaluation strategies beyond aggregate accuracy.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-21f3a6584dd087d86a2f6b3f1a99f0fd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2df46a60ce12797a8d4e5b624970ede7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ffb0995b3d5e71e709d829e54fcfaf1b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b48bf4c58531cb5d0dde75c4cc92714f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42e98b3a62403949c3551faca51d7a9a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0a1b17e7c0ccc7bf601190f38e3fcdcc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a26f425dc22ccfa6db36dc0592c070a7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e4c751eebce71c2e7277e97601a61b7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-33f36369f99eb44a9ac8690e998af200&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-492adf3459368e3424d113800cf1ad98&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-274e345107d112e4d4358391f4226461&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-77c51309c1da2a8788990e7a8432dfd3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ca6e74b9c2346c262d89440c76e3ac05&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a92919218c93fbc995ef28388a45a264&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-306df29aef0348d52b474a51b48f7864&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1224676ee5f3ecf7b88cc6d4ed3fea11&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-090dd9c7587ef7f5e03426647d58470b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ddabb643ad7982794978859b96daf403</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1777580393</data>
