      <data key="d0">Agent Viability Framework</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The Agent Viability Framework is a theoretical framework that establishes three properties -- monitoring, anticipation, and monotonic restriction -- as individually necessary and collectively sufficient for documented failure modes.</data>
