    </node>
    <node id="AgentWard">
      <data key="d0">AgentWard</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">AgentWard systematically organizes protection across five stages of autonomous AI agent lifecycle: initialization, input processing, memory, decision-making, and execution.&lt;SEP&gt;AgentWard provides a concrete blueprint for structuring runtime security controls, managing trust propagation, and enforcing execution containment in autonomous AI agents.&lt;SEP&gt;AgentWard integrates stage-specific, heterogeneous controls with cross-layer coordination to intercept threats along their propagation paths.&lt;SEP&gt;AgentWard is a lifecycle security architecture designed for autonomous AI agents to protect against security failures.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d66caa329c3a04aee4985803a47142b6</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1777506826</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="OpenClaw">
      <data key="d0">OpenClaw</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">OpenClaw is a platform where a plugin-native prototype of AgentWard was implemented to demonstrate practical feasibility.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d66caa329c3a04aee4985803a47142b6</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1777506826</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Security Failures">
      <data key="d0">Security Failures</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Security failures in autonomous AI agents can propagate across multiple stages and become apparent only when harmful effects materialize in the environment.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d66caa329c3a04aee4985803a47142b6</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1777506830</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Lifecycle Security Architecture">
      <data key="d0">Lifecycle Security Architecture</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">A lifecycle security architecture is a comprehensive approach to protecting autonomous AI agents across their lifecycle stages.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d66caa329c3a04aee4985803a47142b6</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1777506832</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Defense-in-Depth Architecture">
      <data key="d0">Defense-in-Depth Architecture</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">A defense-in-depth architecture is a security approach that integrates multiple layers of protection to safeguard against various threats.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d66caa329c3a04aee4985803a47142b6</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1777506834</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Runtime Security Controls">
      <data key="d0">Runtime Security Controls</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Runtime security controls refer to the mechanisms implemented within an autonomous AI agent to protect against security failures and threats during execution.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d66caa329c3a04aee4985803a47142b6</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1777506837</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Trust Propagation">
      <data key="d0">Trust Propagation</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Trust propagation refers to the process of managing and controlling the flow of trust within an autonomous AI agent, ensuring that sensitive information and actions are executed securely.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d66caa329c3a04aee4985803a47142b6</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1777506837</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Execution Containment">
      <data key="d0">Execution Containment</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Execution containment refers to the mechanism of isolating and limiting the impact of security failures or threats within an autonomous AI agent, preventing them from spreading to other components or systems.</data>
