    <node id="Vision-Language Models">
      <data key="d0">Vision-Language Models</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Vision-Language Models are proposed as general-purpose tools for scientific data interpretation in astronomy.&lt;SEP&gt;Vision-Language Models have demonstrated strong performance on textbook-style physics problems but frequently fail in dynamic real-world scenarios.&lt;SEP&gt;Vision-Language Models are frequently undermined by object hallucination due to an over-reliance on linguistic priors.&lt;SEP&gt;Vision-language models are AI systems used for evaluating image-text alignment and are increasingly deployed in tasks requiring nuanced image understanding.&lt;SEP&gt;Vision-Language Models are a type of AI model that combines computer vision and natural language processing to enable machines to understand and interpret visual information.&lt;SEP&gt;Vision-Language Models are models that enable joint reasoning over text and images.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-9ac408a983efd5ccb658b88f8bdc1379&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3fae825413dbd09250459cbd5bbfe30c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0b83f3702bd088008cc6feaedfe42bcc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4f986b39741d6de97b65a3c203f1521e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ee6a8292ee988e4d64c218b75e3c5f57&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7a01dcb477b76a4cacbd754ce4561d7e</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1777541088</data>
